Welcome to Ariadne!

To start the installation, please follow these steps:
- create a database for Ariadne to be installed in
- copy the www directory to your webroot and give it a suitable name, eg
'ariadne'.
- copy the file 'ariadne.inc-unix' or 'ariadne.inc-win' to 'ariadne.inc',
depending on your platform.
- edit ariadne.inc, and point $ariadne to the path of the lib directory, eg.
/usr/local/ariadne/lib
- give write grants for www-data to ariadne/lib/configs/ariadne.phtml
- give write grants for www-data to ariadne/files/
- give write grants for www-data to ariadne/lib/configs/svn to allow SVN support
- remove the .htaccess file from the ariadne/www/install/ folder
- point your webbrowser to http://yourhost/ariadne/install/ to start installation.

After a succesful installation:
- remove the www/install folder
- schedule the cleanup script in the bin folder to remove unused files and session data
- remove write access to lib/configs/ariadne.phtml for the www-data user
